/*
 * This Hyperlambda snippet demonstrates how to crop an image by removing a specified number of pixels from one side.
 *
 * 1. [image.crop]
 *    * Initiates the cropping operation on the specified image file.
 *    * The image file is located at "/modules/test/qr.png".
 *
 * 2. [right]
 *    * Specifies the number of pixels to be removed from the right side of the image.
 *    * In this example, 50 pixels are removed from the right.
 */
image.crop:/modules/test/qr.png
   right:50